{"title_page": "Naughty Boy", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| image            = Naughtyboyasianawards.png\n| caption          = Naughty Boy at the fifth annual Asian Awards (2015)\n| name             = Naughty Boy\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = Shahid Khan\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1985|1|1}}\n| birth_place      = [[Watford]], England\n| origin           = Watford, England\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[UK garage]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Pop music|pop]]|}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|DJ|record producer|songwriter|musician|rapper|singer}}\n| years_active     = 2005\u2013present\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Emeli Sand\u00e9]]|[[Leona Lewis]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|hotel-cabana.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Shahid Khan''' ({{lang-ur|\u0634\u0627\u0647\u062f \u062e\u0627\u0646}}; born 1 January 1985),<ref name=bbc2013 /> known by his stage name '''Naughty Boy''', is a British DJ, [[record producer]], songwriter and musician. In 2012, Shahid Khan signed a three\u2013year publishing deal with [[Sony/ATV Music Publishing|Sony ATV]], as well as a recording contract to release one album under [[Virgin EMI Records]]. Shahid Khan launched himself as a record producer under the moniker \"Naughty Boy\" and runs his own production company called Naughty Boy Recordings.\n\nHe has produced two records for UK rappers [[Chipmunk (rapper)|Chipmunk]] and [[Wiley (rapper)|Wiley]], both featuring [[Emeli Sand\u00e9]]. Naughty Boy and Sand\u00e9 later formed a writing and production partnership, leading to Sand\u00e9 landing her own record deal with Virgin and EMI. Sand\u00e9 went on to be named the Critics Choice for the [[2012 BRIT Awards]], and release her debut album ''[[Our Version of Events]]'' (2012), a record co-written and produced with Naughty Boy. Shahid Khan spent the 2011 and 2012 working on records for [[Leona Lewis]], [[JLS]], [[Cheryl (singer)|Cheryl]], [[Jennifer Hudson]], [[Alesha Dixon]] and [[Tinie Tempah]], among others.\n\nIn 2013, Naughty Boy released his debut album ''[[Hotel Cabana]]''. The set features prominent collaborator Sand\u00e9, as well as [[Ed Sheeran]], [[Gabrielle (singer)|Gabrielle]] and others. It was preceded by the release of the top-ten single \"[[Wonder (Naughty Boy song)|Wonder]]\" (featuring Sand\u00e9), the number one hit \"[[La La La (Naughty Boy song)|La La La]]\", featuring [[Sam Smith (singer)|Sam Smith]] and \"[[Lifted (Naughty Boy song)|Lifted]]\", another collaboration with Sand\u00e9. His debut album peaked at number two in the UK.\n\nOn 19 October 2013, Naughty Boy's \"La La La\" was awarded 'Best Song' and 'Best Video' at the [[MOBO Awards|MOBO Award's]] 18th Anniversary.<ref>{{cite news|title=Naughty Boy Wins Two MOBO's at the 18th Anniversary Awards |url=http://whatsgoodonline.co.uk/events/mobo-award-winners-2013-announced/ |accessdate=19 October 2013 |newspaper=What's Good? Online |date=19 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020131900/http://whatsgoodonline.co.uk/events/mobo-award-winners-2013-announced/ |archivedate=20 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nShahid Khan was born on 1 January 1985 in [[Watford]], Hertfordshire.<ref name=bbc2013>{{cite news | url = https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-23703742| title=Naughty Boy: From Watford to number one | first= Mark |last=Savage| work=[[BBC News]]| date=16 August 2013|accessdate=31 March 2015| quote = Born Shahid Khan on New Year's Day 1985, Naughty Boy grew up in a terraced house in Watford.}}</ref> His parents being originally from [[Pakistan]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Savage |first=Mark |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-23703742 |title=BBC News \u2013 Naughty Boy: From Watford to number one |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=16 August 2013 |accessdate=2013-08-22}}</ref> and explaining the importance of his [[Pakistani identity]], having also been into a school near [[Rawalpindi]] for two years, he says that he grew up listening to [[Pakistani music]] and watching [[Pakistani movies]] more than being influenced by [[Western culture]], admiring the likes of [[Sultan Rahi]] and [[Mustafa Qureshi]], ultimately professing that \"I am a very proud Pakistani and I celebrate that\".<ref>Murtaza Ali Shah (3 January 2019), [https://www.geo.tv/latest/224026-pakistan-defines-me-but-i-wanted-western-audience-to-know-my-music-first-says-british-pakistani-dj-naughty-boy \"'Pakistan defines me but I wanted Western audience to know my music first', says British-Pakistani DJ Naughty Boy\"], ''Geo News''. Retrieved 25 January 2019.</ref> Initially, Shahid Khan was studying Business and Marketing at [[London Guildhall University]] (now London Metropolitan University), but during his first semester, he decided to drop out and did various part-time jobs in [[Domino's Pizza]] and [[Watford General Hospital]].<ref name=\"This is London 2009\"/><ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/news/5049729.Watford_music_producer_notches_up_another_chart_hit/ |title=Watford Music Producer Notches Up Another Chart Hit |work=Watford Observer |date=9 March 2012 |accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref> He won \u00a344,000 on ''[[Deal or No Deal (UK game show)|Deal or No Deal]]'' and spent the money on a studio in his parent's garden. He \"decided to follow his ambition to write and produce his own music, under the name Naughty Boy Recordings.\"<ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/> In the background, Shahid Khan was recording songs in his parents' garden shed in Charlock Way in [[Watford]], Hertfordshire.<ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/> The finances allowed Shahid Khan to upscale production from the garden shed to a studio in [[Ealing]], West London. Eventually, he got a three-year contract with [[Sony/ATV Music Publishing|Sony ATV]], and a one-album record deal with [[Virgin Records]] ([[EMI|EMI Records]]).<ref name=\"This is London 2009\"/><ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/>\n\nShahid Khan applied to [[The Princes Trust]] in 2005, where he was awarded a grant of \u00a35,000 to help start up his business. Speaking to the ''Watford Observer'' in 2009 about the opportunity, Shahid Khan said \"The Prince's Trust has a scheme where they want to help people who they feel can set up their own business. I wanted to make music but I didn't have any equipment. They said they wanted to help me.\"<ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/> That same year, Shahid Khan appeared on [[Channel 4]]'s hit day-time gameshow ''[[Deal or No Deal (UK game show)|Deal or No Deal]]'', where he won \u00a344,000, further enabling him to purchase equipment and begin recording.<ref name=\"This is London 2009\"/> The producer now bases his recordings at his studio in [[Ealing]], West London.<ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/>\nHe also provides the voice for Gecko, in the popular YouTube children\u2019s series ''Gecko\u2019s Garage''.{{fact|date=August 2018}}\n\n== Music career ==\n\n=== 2009\u201312: Beginnings and producing ===\n[[File:Emeli Sand\u00e9 NRJ Music Awards 2013.jpg|thumb|right|140px|[[Emeli Sand\u00e9]] frequently writes with Naughty Boy.]]\nThe producer burst on to the music scene in 2009, by co-writing and producing [[Chipmunk (rapper)|Chipmunk]]'s hit single \"[[Diamond Rings (song)|Diamond Rings]]\", featuring [[Emeli Sand\u00e9]].<ref name=\"This is London 2009\">{{cite web |url=http://www.thisislocallondon.co.uk/news/4528790.Watford_producer_scores_chart_hit/ |title=Naughty Boy helps others achieve music stardom after writing chart hit Diamond Rings |work=This Is London |date=5 August 2012  |accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref> Shahid Khan would once again work with Sand\u00e9, this time on [[Wiley (rapper)|Wiley]]'s \"[[Never Be Your Woman]]\" (2010), a cover of [[White Town]]'s \"[[Your Woman]]\" (1997).<ref name=\"This is London 2009\"/> Sand\u00e9 later earned a record deal with Virgin Records, with Shahid Khan co-writing and producing her debut album, ''[[Our Version of Events]]''. Naughty Boy was formally introduced and credited as an artist on Sand\u00e9's second single \"[[Daddy (Emeli Sand\u00e9 song)|Daddy]]\", though he doesn't actually perform on the track.\n\nShahid Khan has also worked with [[Alesha Dixon]], [[JLS]], [[Lily Allen]], [[Alexandra Burke]] and [[Jennifer Hudson]].<ref name=\"This is London 2009\"/><ref name=\"Watford Observer 17 Aug 2012\"/> He also produced records for [[Professor Green]], [[Cheryl Cole]] and [[Tinie Tempah]].<ref name=\"4 Music Aug 2012\"/> Shahid Khan worked with Sand\u00e9 to produce and co-write [[Leona Lewis]]' 2012 comeback single \"Trouble\" which features [[Childish Gambino]].<ref name=\"PR Release\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dawbell.com/news/leona_lewis_returns_with_her_brand_new_single_-_trouble_featuring_childish_ |title=Leona Lewis returns with her brand new single \u2013 'Trouble' featuring Childish Gambino |publisher=[[Syco Music]] & [[Sony Music]] through DawBell Press & Media |date=August 2012 |accessdate=17 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825001859/http://www.dawbell.com/news/leona_lewis_returns_with_her_brand_new_single_-_trouble_featuring_childish_ |archivedate=25 August 2012}}</ref> Shahid Khan also wrote and produced \"When It Hurts\" and \"Mountains\" for Lewis' album ''[[Glassheart]]''; However, \"Mountains\" was re-recorded by Sand\u00e9 and put on her own album ''[[Our Version of Events]]''.<ref name=\"Digital Spy 15 Aug 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a399620/leona-lewis-demos-leak-online-listen.html |title=Music \u2013 Leona Lewis demos leak online \u2013 listen |publisher=Digital Spy (Hearst Media) |last=Corner |first=Lewis |date=15 August 2012 |accessdate=16 August 2012}}</ref> He also worked on records for [[Rihanna]] including \"[[Half of Me (Rihanna song)|Half of Me]]\" (co-produced with [[Stargate (production team)|Stargate]]),<ref name=\"Unapologetic Credits\">[[Rihanna]] \u2013 ''[[Unapologetic (album)|Unapologetic]]''. [album credits]. SRP / [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam Records]].</ref> \"Side Effects of You\" for [[Fantasia Barrino]]<ref name=\"SEOU Credits\">[[Fantasia Barrino]] \u2013 ''[[Side Effects of You]]''. [Album Booklet]. [[19 Recordings|19]] / [[RCA Records]]</ref> and co-produced \"Craziest Things\" with [[will.i.am]] for [[Cheryl Cole]].<ref name=\"AML Credits\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/a-million-lights-mw0002365468/credits|title= Personnel;\u2013 Credits|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation|accessdate=25 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== 2012\u201314: ''Hotel Cabana'' ===\n{{main article|Hotel Cabana}}\nShahid Khan also spent time, throughout the development of his career, working on his own debut album titled ''[[Hotel Cabana]]'', which was scheduled to be released under his moniker \"Naughty Boy\" by [[Virgin EMI Records]] in 2013.<ref name=\"4 Music Aug 2012\">{{cite web|url=http://www.4music.com/news/news/5639/First-Listen-Naughty-Boy-ft.-Emeli-Sande-Wonder |title=First Listen \u2013 Naughty Boy & Emeli Sand\u00e9 \u2013 Wonder |publisher=[[4 Music]] |accessdate=16 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131010010257/http://www.4music.com/news/news/5639/First-Listen-Naughty-Boy-ft.-Emeli-Sande-Wonder |archivedate=10 October 2013 }}</ref> The album's first single \"[[Wonder (Naughty Boy song)|Wonder]]\" features frequent collaborator Sand\u00e9 on the lead vocals.<ref>[http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a399090/emeli-sande-features-on-new-naughty-boy-single-wonder-listen.html Digital Spy]. Digital Spy (13 August 2012).</ref> It was released on 30 September 2012 and also was the [[lead single|leading single]] from the re-release of Sand\u00e9's debut album, ''[[Our Version of Events]]'', after already appearing on the US version of the album.<ref name=\"Fifth Single\">{{cite web| first=Lewis | last=Corner |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a399090/emeli-sande-features-on-new-naughty-boy-single-wonder-listen.html |title=Emeli Sand\u00e9 features on new Naughty Boy single 'Wonder' \u2013 listen \u2013 Music News |website=Digital Spy |date=13 August 2012 |accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> It peaked at number ten on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref>[https://archive.today/20130411225137/http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2012-11-03/ 3 November 2012 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive]. Official Charts (3 November 2012).</ref>\n\nBritish singer [[Gabrielle (singer)|Gabrielle]] also worked with Naughty Boy for ''Hotel Cabana'' on a song called \"Hollywood\", which was initially tipped to be the album's second single, with the album following in February 2013.<ref name=\"Gabby\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gabrielle.co.uk/naughty-boy-produced-new-single-hollywood-due-november/ |title=Gabrielle to feature on Naughty Boy song \"Hollywood\" |publisher=Gabrielle.co.uk |date= |accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/jan13/articles/shahid-khan.htm |title=Khan Do |publisher=Soundonsound.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-08}}</ref> Gabrielle also revealed that fellow British singer-songwriter [[Ed Sheeran]] and British rapper [[Tinie Tempah]] will also feature on ''Hotel Cabana''.<ref name=\"Gabby\"/> Both Tempah and Sheeran have worked with Naughty Boy on previous records. It is the album's title song, \"Hotel Cabana\" which features Tempah.<ref name=\"Hotel Cabana song\">{{cite web |url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/writer.asp?page=1&blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True&fromrow=1&torow=25&affiliation=PRS&cae=531039880&keyID=1201897&keyname=KHAN%20SHAHID&querytype=WriterID |title=HOTEL CABANA (Legal Title) BMI Work #13137712 |publisher=BMI Repertoire (Broadcast Music Incorporated) |accessdate=20 August 2012 }}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> A trailer for ''Hotel Cabana'' was premiered on Naughty Boy's [[Vevo]] account on 20 September 2012. It states ''Hotel Cabana'' is \"directed by Naughty Boy, starring Emeli Sand\u00e9, Tinie Tempah, Professor Green, Gabrielle and [[George the Poet]]\".<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TUpCGAZkXUE |title=Naughty Boy \u2013 Hotel Cabana (Trailer) |publisher=YouTube |date=20 September 2012}}</ref> Of the album, Shahid Khan's opinion of it was \"It has a concept to it, so it's more like a film in some respects\", claiming \"I'm not just a producer \u2013 I'm a director too\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereoboard.com/content/view/175044/9#ixzz27zwgQpWo |title=Naughty Boy Releases 'Hotel Cabana' Album Trailer Feat. Professor Green, Tinie Tempah & More \u2013 Stereoboard UK |publisher=Stereoboard.com |date=25 September 2012}}</ref> However, it did not happen until May 2013, that the second single \"[[La La La (Naughty Boy song)|La La La]]\" featuring [[Sam Smith (singer)|Sam Smith]] was released. It reached number one in the UK,<ref>[https://archive.today/20130615081335/http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2013-06-01/ 1 June 2013 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive]. Official Charts (1 June 2013).</ref> three in Ireland<ref>[http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2013&year=2013&week=24 GFK Chart-Track] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116113127/http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2013&year=2013&week=24 |date=16 November 2018 }}. Chart-track.co.uk.</ref> and three in Scotland.<ref>[http://www.theofficialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/22/2013-06-01/ 1 June 2013 Top 40 Scottish Singles Archive]. Official Charts (1 June 2013).</ref> The album was released on 26 August 2013.<ref name=\"HC Release\"/> It peaked at number two in the UK.\n\nAfter completing work on his own album, in 2013, Shahid Khan resumed production for other artists. He worked on pop records for American singer [[Britney Spears]], as well as joining Spears' sessions with producer [[William Orbit]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Carl Williott |url=http://idolator.com/7474488/britney-spears-new-album-naughty-boy |title=Naughty Boy Says He's Avoiding Dubstep on Britney Spears' New Album &#124; Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on |publisher=Idolator.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-08}}</ref> British singer [[Lily Allen]] also asked Shahid Khan to produce records for her upcoming album.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chi |first=Chi |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/23341065 |title=Newsbeat \u2013 Naughty Boy producing Lily Allen's third studio album |publisher=BBC |date=18 July 2013 |accessdate=2013-08-08}}</ref> Additionally, he teamed up with Sand\u00e9 and [[Katy Perry]] in New York to work on a song for Perry's then upcoming album, ''[[Prism (Katy Perry album)|Prism]]'' (2013).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.3news.co.nz/Emeli-Sande-writing-for-Britney-Spears-and-Katy-Perry/tabid/418/articleID/312179/Default.aspx |title=Emeli Sande writing for Britney Spears and Katy Perry \u2013 Story \u2013 Entertainment |publisher=3 News |date= |accessdate=2014-05-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512220228/http://www.3news.co.nz/Emeli-Sande-writing-for-Britney-Spears-and-Katy-Perry/tabid/418/articleID/312179/Default.aspx |archive-date=12 May 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===2015\u2013present: ''The X Factor'' and second album===\nIn March 2015, it was confirmed that Naughty Boy had worked with then-[[One Direction]] member [[Zayn Malik]] for one of the tracks of his second album.<ref>{{cite web|title=Naughty Boy confirma que ha trabajado con Zayn Malik|url=http://los40.com/los40/2015/03/03/actualidad/1425370725_540360.html|website=Los 40 Principales|accessdate=29 March 2015|location=Spain|language=Spanish|date=3 March 2015}}</ref> Malik exited the band shortly after this announcement, which led to many One Direction fans blaming Naughty Boy for Malik's departure.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cox|first1=Lauren|title=Zayn Malik: Fans Furious He\u2019s Making New Solo Music With Naughty Boy|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2015/03/27/zayn-malik-fans-angry-solo-music-naughty-boy/|website=Hollywood Life|accessdate=29 March 2015|date=27 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 September 2015, Naughty Boy announced that he would release a song titled \"[[Runnin' (Lose It All)]]\" featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and Arrow Benjamin. On the same date, he shared the artwork for the single, its lyrics, a 15-second sound snippet along with a video through his [[Instagram]] account and began a countdown until its online release.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/16/naughty-boy-beyonce-runnin-lose-it-all-teaser|title=Naughty Boy teases new song with Beyonc\u00e9|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|first=Eric|last=Renner Brown|date=16 September 2015|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"bill\">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6699687/beyonce-naughty-boy-runnin-lose-it-all|title=New Beyonce! Naughty Boy Previews Their Song 'Runnin' (Lose It All)'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|first=Erin|last=Strecker|date=16 September 2015|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref> The following day, on 17 September 2015, \"Runnin' (Lose It All)\" premiered online. It was available for digital download on the [[iTunes Store]] on 18 September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/runnin-lose-it-all-feat.-beyonce/id1039397480|title=Runnin' (Lose It All) [feat. Beyonc\u00e9 & Arrow Benjamin] \u2013 Single by Naughty Boy|publisher=[[iTunes Store]] (UK). [[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=19 September 2015}}</ref> \"[[Should've Been Me]]\", featuring vocals from [[Kyla (British singer)|Kyla]] and [[Popcaan]] was released as the second single on 18 November 2016. The song has peaked at number 61 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. \"One Chance to Dance\", featuring vocals from [[Joe Jonas]] was released as the third single on 20 October 2017.\n\nOn 13 September 2017, Naughty Boy released a reworked edition of the Jackson 5's song \"[[Dancing Machine]]\" featuring vocals from [[Laura Mvula]] under the name of \"Naughty Town\", from an upcoming Motown covers album.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/naughty-boy-wants-to-bring-motown-to-millennials-with-new-album-they-will-understand-it-more-than-a3652136.html|title=Naughty Boy wants to bring Motown to millennials with new album|work=Evening Standard|access-date=2018-01-27}}</ref> According ''[[The Evening Standard]]'', Naughty Boy has also collaborated with [[Justin Timberlake]] and [[Dua Lipa]] on the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/naughty-boy-wants-to-bring-motown-to-millennials-with-new-album-they-will-understand-it-more-than-a3652136.html|title=Naughty Boy wants to bring Motown to millennials with new album|date=6 October 2017|website=Evening Standard}}</ref> In December 2017, Naughty Boy along with [[Wyclef Jean]] appeared on the final of the [[The X Factor (UK series 14)|fourteenth series]] of ''[[The X Factor (UK TV series)|The X Factor]]'', guest performing \"[[Dimelo (Rak-Su song)|Dimelo]]\" with contestants [[Rak-Su]], his fellow Watford natives. Rak-Su won and the performance was released as the winner's single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42217568|title=X Factor 2017 winner announced|date=4 December 2017|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, Naughty Boy announced his second album had experienced some delays due to legal issues; he wanted to call the album ''Now That's What I Call Naughty'', but was legally challenged over its similarity to the ''[[Now That's What I Call Music!]]'' compilation album series.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/98362-naughty-boy-album-delayed-due-to-naming-issues/|title=Naughty Boy album delayed due to naming issues|date=2018-01-08|work=The List|access-date=2018-01-16}}</ref> Describing the album as a [[playlist]], he said \"with my new album I wanted to make a real sick playlist that anyone and everyone can listen to.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/hits-radio/entertainment/music/naughty-boy-album-delay/|title=Naughty Boy reveals the unusual reason his album is delayed|date=8 January 2018|website=Hits Radio}}</ref> At the time of writing, he had completed studio sessions with [[Dua Lipa]], [[Mike Posner]], [[MNEK]], [[Ray BLK]], [[Joe Jonas]], [[WizKid]], [[Bebe Rexha]], [[Paloma Faith]], [[Tom Walker (singer)|Tom Walker]], [[Miguel (singer)|Miguel]], [[Calum Scott]], [[Shenseea]], [[Popcaan]], [[Kyla]], [[Ray BLK]], [[Wyclef Jean]], [[Craig David]] and [[Julia Michaels]] but refused to confirm which were for his own album.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"vents\">{{cite web|url=https://ventsmagazine.com/2018/12/07/naughty-boy-releases-bungee-jumping-feat-emeli-sande-rahat-fateh-ali-khan/|title=Naughty Boy Releases 'Bungee Jumping' feat. Emeli Sand\u00e9 & Rahat Fateh Ali Khan|website=Vents Magazine|last=Frometa|first=Rj|date=7 December 2018|accessdate=28 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April 2018, he released his collaboration with artist [[Ray BLK]] and [[Wyclef Jean]] titled \"All or Nothing\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/04/17/naughty-boy-all-or-nothing-ray-blk-wyclef-jean|title=Naughty Boy debuts 'All Or Nothing' with Ray BLK and Wyclef|website=The Fader}}</ref> On 7 December 2018, \"Bungee Jumping\" was released featuring vocals from [[Emeli Sand\u00e9]] and [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]].\nOn 22 March 2019, \"Undo\" was released featuring [[Calum Scott]] and Jamaican dancehall artist Shenseea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/naughty-boy-teams-up-with-calum-scott-and-shenseea-for-new-track-undo/|title=Naughty Boy teams up with Calum Scott and Shenseea for new track Undo|date=23 March 2019|website=entertainment-focus.com}}</ref> At the time of writing (April 2019) Naughty Boy's second studio album was set for release in Autumn 2019.<ref name=\"vents\"/> From 9 - 15 December, Naughty Boy appeared was part of the 'industry' panel for ''The X Factor'' spin off series, ''[[The X Factor: The Band]]'', launched to try and find the UK's next biggest band.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-12-09/naughty-boy-x-factor-the-band/ |title=Who is X Factor: The Band industry expert Naughty Boy |work=[[Radio Times]] |publisher=[[Immediate Media Company|Immediate Media Co]] |last=Furn |first=Daniel |date=9 December 2019 |accessdate=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"7\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br/><ref name=\"UKAlbums\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/naughty%20boy/| title=Naughty Boy|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|format=select \"Albums\" tab}}</ref>\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref name=\"AUS Albums\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/digital-albums |title=ARIA Digital Albums Chart |publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) |date=9 September 2013 |accessdate=9 September 2013 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131012175649/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/digital-albums |archive-date=12 October 2013 |url-status=dea